    "title_en": "Ghost Hunting in the Yang-Mills Vacuum",
    "abstract_en": "In this work, I analyze the zero modes of a one-loop semiclassical Yang-Mills theory in \\(3+1\\)d. I find that zero modes are generated by gauge redundancy of the background field. Proper gauge fixing, achieved by introducing a bosonic ghost term, together with zeta-function regularization, yields a finite one-loop effective action in closed form that reproduces the well-known one-loop Yang-Mills beta function.",
